Initial files that already exist before the agent starts:

Path: /home/user/hardening/config.json  
Contents:  
{
  "system": "webserver",
  "ssh": {
    "permitRootLogin": "no",
    "passwordAuthentication": "no"
  },
  "firewall": {
    "portsOpen": [22, 80, 443]
  }
}

Path: /home/user/hardening/schema.json  
Contents:  
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["system", "ssh", "firewall"],
  "properties": {
    "system": { "type": "string" },
    "ssh": {
      "type": "object",
      "required": ["permitRootLogin", "passwordAuthentication"],
      "properties": {
        "permitRootLogin": {
          "type": "string",
          "enum": ["yes", "no"]
        },
        "passwordAuthentication": {
          "type": "string",
          "enum": ["yes", "no"]
        }
      },
      "additionalProperties": false
    },
    "firewall": {
      "type": "object",
      "required": ["portsOpen"],
      "properties": {
        "portsOpen": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": { "type": "integer" }
        }
      },
      "additionalProperties": false
    }
  },
  "additionalProperties": false
}

Expected state after the agent completes the task:

1. /home/user/hardening/validation.log  
   VALID\n  (exactly five characters “VALID” plus a single newline, nothing else).

2. /home/user/hardening/open_ports.txt  
   22\n80\n443\nTOTAL: 3\n  
   (Each number and the TOTAL line end with a newline, no blank line after TOTAL).

3. /home/user/hardening/config_hardened.json  
   {
     "system": "webserver",
     "ssh": {
       "permitRootLogin": "no",
       "passwordAuthentication": "no"
     },
     "firewall": {
       "portsOpen": [
         22,
         443
       ]
     }
   }\n  
   (Two-space indentation, newline at EOF, no port 80 present).

File permissions: all new files should be user-writable (default 644 is fine).  
No other files should be created or modified.
